OL,6,FJohn Richardson, prosecuting, said Ms
OL,7,FDoyle had lived with her parents for
OL,8,F22 years before moving into her own
OL,9,Fhouse with full-time carers.
OL,11,FShe was entitled to payments from the
OL,12,Fcouncil, which were initially managed
OL,13,Fby her mum Lilian and her sister.
OL,15,FMr Richardson said: "The other carers
OL,16,Fbecame concerned about the running of
OL,17,Fthe finances and items that were being
OL,18,Fdelivered that were clearly not for
OL,19,FAlison, and matters were brought to
OL,20,Fthe police.
