OL,6,F"You were employed to protect and care
OL,7,Ffor her and instead you exploited her
OL,8,Fposition for your own gain."
OL,10,FHatzer, of Mortlake Drive, was jailed
OL,11,Ffor 60 weeks, of which she will serve
OL,12,Fhalf in prison before being released
OL,13,Fon licence. She was made the subject
OL,14,Fof a restraining order banning her
OL,15,Ffrom contacting Ms Doyle or her family
OL,16,Ffor five years.
